The Dutch transport, trading andstorage firm PHS Van Ommeren NV &lt;OMMN.AS> said it plans a 75mln guilder bond issue with warrants attached.    The bond will have a maturity of 10 years with repayment inthe second five year period in equal yearly instalments.    Each bond of 1,000 guilders nominal has five "A" warrants and20 "B" warrants attached. Each warrant entitles the holder toacquire one non-cancellable share certificate. The exerciseperiod of the "A" warrants will be three years and of the "B"warrants five years.     Coupon and price of the bond issue as well as the exerciseprice of the warrants will be announced April 27 after theclose of the Amsterdam Stock Exchange. REUTER&#3;